00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:39,500
Whoa, seriously?

506
00:19:39,583 --> 00:19:41,791
I guess it's better than
having nothing to do, right?

507
00:19:41,875 --> 00:19:43,875
Let's just keep an eye on them.

508
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:45,333
Where's Yoshino?

509
00:19:45,416 --> 00:19:47,916
The professor called her,
so she went over to see him.

510
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,125
The professor?

511
00:19:49,208 --> 00:19:50,375
--Whoa.
--What is it?

512
00:19:50,458 --> 00:19:51,875
A fight is breaking out.

513
00:19:51,958 --> 00:19:54,875
[SANAE] "I'm coming over
to kick your ass, Goro."

514
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:57,416
[SANAE] Hm?!
Wait, this is an actual threat!

515
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,708
Who the hell wrote that?

516
00:19:58,791 --> 00:20:01,333
We'd better get over
to Goro's place right now!

517
00:20:01,416 --> 00:20:02,875
[SHIGE]
You fat young punk!

518
00:20:02,958 --> 00:20:05,125
I should have known it
was you who threatened me!

519
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:06,333
You're imagining things!

520
00:20:06,416 --> 00:20:08,166
Where's your proof,
you skinny old corpse?

521
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:09,458
Would you stop it, you two?

522
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:10,916
You're both well over
eighty years old!

523
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:12,041
[SANAE]
What's going on?

524
00:20:13,416 --> 00:20:15,166
[SHIGE] This guy is constantly
making fun of me!

525
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:17,000
Making sneaky remarks online!

526
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:18,916
[GORO]
I'd say it to your face!

527
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:22,250
When would I have taken
that picture, anyway?

528
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:24,500
[RIRIKO] "Look at Shige's
tiny little cucumbers!

529
00:20:24,583 --> 00:20:25,583
They're cracking me up!"

530
00:20:25,666 --> 00:20:26,958
[SHIORI]
Huh?

531
00:20:27,041 --> 00:20:28,875
Okay, okay, we got it!
Now let's calm down, please!

532
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:30,208
We're going to start
making everyone

533
00:20:30,291 --> 00:20:32,916
use their real names
from now on.

534
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,958
[YOSHINO]
Are you serious?

535
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:36,375
Yeah. Yeah, okay.

536
00:20:36,458 --> 00:20:37,583
I'll head right back.

537
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:39,750
Thanks to you
and your friends,

538
00:20:39,833 --> 00:20:42,041
my friends and I have
actually learned quite a bit.

539
00:20:42,125 --> 00:20:43,458
Thank you for that.

540
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:46,666
Well, looks like we've
created some problems, too.

541
00:20:46,750 --> 00:20:49,000
At the dawn of
the internet, it was different.

542
00:20:49,083 --> 00:20:50,416
People had to
register to use it,

543
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,791
so they were more courteous.

544
00:20:51,875 --> 00:20:53,541
Then, screen names
were introduced,

545
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:54,958
encouraging lawlessness.

546
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:58,083
Next came flat-rate
plans creating shut-ins.

547
00:20:58,166 --> 00:20:59,291
[chuckles]

548
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:01,291
History has a way of
repeating itself, huh?

549
00:21:01,375 --> 00:21:03,250
I don't know that it's
anything to laugh about.

550
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,375
And remember, you were the
one who encouraged Sanae

551
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:06,958
to do this in the first place!

552
00:21:07,041 --> 00:21:10,166
[SUZUHARA] Well, I
suppose the time is right.

553
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,500
Ms. Koharu.

554
00:21:11,583 --> 00:21:12,708
I'm terribly sorry,

555
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:15,625
but I'm going to have
to take you hostage.

556
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:16,750
What, now?

557
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:20,875
[SHIORI]
Yoshi sure is late tonight.

558
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:22,708
She said she'd be
right back, didn't she?

559
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:25,250
She did. I wonder
if something happened.

560
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:27,375
--[RIRIKO gasps]
--What is it this time?

561
00:21:27,458 --> 00:21:29,208
The professor's house.

562
00:21:29,291 --> 00:21:31,083
[SUZUHARA] We, the people
of Warabiya village,

563
00:21:31,166 --> 00:21:33,250
wish to express our
opposition to the removal

564
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:34,625
of our bus route,

565
00:21:34,708 --> 00:21:37,583
as well our deep
disillusionment and rage.

566
00:21:37,666 --> 00:21:39,958
People are the
foundation of the state.

567
00:21:40,041 --> 00:21:42,750
If you deem it necessary
to forsake us,

568
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:45,583
then we will be forced
to do the same to you.

569
00:21:45,666 --> 00:21:48,000
In light of that,
we hereby withdraw

570
00:21:48,083 --> 00:21:50,250
from the Kingdom of Chupakabura!

571
00:21:50,333 --> 00:21:51,375
What?!

572
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:52,583
They're withdrawing
from the Kingdom?

573
00:21:52,666 --> 00:21:54,333
But not from Manoyama?

574
00:21:54,416 --> 00:21:56,166
For real,
what is he talking about?

575
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:57,500
Hey, look over there!

576
00:21:57,583 --> 00:21:58,791
It's Yoshi!

577
00:21:58,875 --> 00:22:01,458
[MAKI] Girl, what is
going on with you?

578
00:22:01,541 --> 00:22:06,333
[SENIORS]
Hey hey, ho! Hey, ho!

579
00:22:06,416 --> 00:22:07,416
Ho.

580
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,541
[SANDAL] My cousin wouldn't
listen to his dad, my uncle,

581
00:23:41,625 --> 00:23:43,583
for five whole years
after my uncle forgot

582
00:23:43,666 --> 00:23:45,666
to erase his browsing history.

583
00:23:45,750 --> 00:23:48,000
Next time:
"Minerva's Saké Saucer."

